WEBVTT

01:42.000 --> 01:43.666
- Hello!
-  Hi!

01:43.666 --> 01:46.500
Hello, Presleys. I'm Barbara.

01:46.500 --> 01:47.791
So nice to meet you.

01:47.791 --> 01:49.500
Nice to meet you!

01:49.500 --> 01:51.458
I know. I know it's a little rough,

01:51.458 --> 01:54.333
but nothing
a little landscaping couldn't fix, right?

01:55.625 --> 01:57.500
- What about this porch?
-  Yeah.

01:57.500 --> 02:00.125
Huh? Original everything.

02:01.083 --> 02:03.416
-  Everyone here?
-  Uh-huh.

02:03.416 --> 02:04.333
Ready?

02:04.333 --> 02:05.833
- Yeah. Let's see it.
- Okay.

02:11.750 --> 02:12.875
Everything okay?

02:13.416 --> 02:16.833
Oh! Yes! Come in. Come in!

02:19.125 --> 02:21.083
Cleaning crew can't come until Tuesday.

02:21.583 --> 02:22.583
As you can see,

02:24.125 --> 02:26.583
the home has tons of old-world charm.

02:27.791 --> 02:30.291
The house was built in 1904.

02:30.291 --> 02:34.333
It's registered with the Illinois
Historic Preservation Society.

02:34.333 --> 02:36.208
Instant value added.

02:36.208 --> 02:38.958
And look at all the gorgeous...

02:41.541 --> 02:42.375
Where's Kevin?

02:43.250 --> 02:46.250
<i>♪ I used to be such a sweet, sweet thing ♪</i>

02:46.250 --> 02:49.458
<i>♪ Till they got a hold of me ♪</i>

02:50.916 --> 02:52.375
<i>♪ I opened doors... ♪</i>

02:52.375 --> 02:53.458
What are you doing?

02:54.791 --> 02:56.458
<i>- ♪ I helped the... ♪</i>

02:59.250 --> 03:00.375
Come inside.

03:01.083 --> 03:02.291
Do I have to?

03:02.291 --> 03:03.666
Yes, you have to.

03:38.041 --> 03:39.750
Tons of closet space, huh?

03:41.083 --> 03:45.083
Primary bath, original fixtures and tile.

03:45.083 --> 03:48.375
Oh! And have you noticed
the high ceilings? I mean...

03:49.250 --> 03:50.958
The house is just listed really low.

03:51.916 --> 03:54.583
And I know it's a fixer-upper, but still...

03:54.583 --> 03:58.666
- Nothing, like, bad happened here, right?

03:59.833 --> 04:02.083
Oh my...

04:03.875 --> 04:07.291
Oh my gosh, no.
It's just a buyer's market.

06:09.875 --> 06:11.166
Got ya, bitch.

06:11.166 --> 06:13.583
- Ha, ha, ha. You got me. Ha.

06:15.833 --> 06:17.541
- Were you there the whole time?
- Yeah.

06:17.541 --> 06:19.583
- Oh my God.
- It took you long enough.

06:19.583 --> 06:21.958
Got me messing up my drip
with all this dust.

06:23.916 --> 06:26.041
...little work, yard work
or anything like that.

06:26.041 --> 06:28.000
You know what I'm saying? Oh!

06:29.625 --> 06:31.916
Think we're gonna move here?

06:31.916 --> 06:33.458
Hell no, man.

06:33.458 --> 06:34.708
This place is a dump.

06:36.916 --> 06:39.125
Watch your right side.
Come in tight!

06:40.416 --> 06:42.250
No, no, no. Turn more.

06:42.250 --> 06:43.750
Hey, wait! No, no, no!

06:44.833 --> 06:47.166
Hey, watch it! You hit the mailbox, man!

06:56.791 --> 07:00.083
There's ten more of those on the truck,
and they ain't moving themselves.

07:05.041 --> 07:05.958
Funny.

07:21.958 --> 07:23.083
Oi, Joy!

07:42.291 --> 07:43.583
Nasty.

07:44.166 --> 07:46.583
Nasty. Nasty.

07:47.500 --> 07:49.750
- Nasty. Nasty.

07:50.416 --> 07:51.833
Nasty.

07:55.000 --> 07:56.208
Ooh.

07:58.333 --> 07:59.458
What are you doing?

08:02.875 --> 08:04.833
Oh yeah.

08:07.500 --> 08:08.416
Come on.

08:09.375 --> 08:11.708
- It's a dance party, man.

08:11.708 --> 08:13.291
Pick something good.

08:13.291 --> 08:15.625
- Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

08:15.625 --> 08:17.541
Come on, man. It's a dance party, Kev.

08:17.541 --> 08:19.625
Remember you used to dance
with your old man? Come on.

08:19.625 --> 08:21.375
-  Show me some of them moves.

08:21.375 --> 08:23.583
Come on. Look! Come on.

08:31.750 --> 08:32.750
Come on, man.

08:33.500 --> 08:35.291
I'm good, Dad. Thanks.

08:36.875 --> 08:39.791
<i>♪ Who knew we'd make it this far ♪</i>

08:39.791 --> 08:42.458
<i>- ♪ Then I think about where would I be-- ♪</i>

08:46.625 --> 08:48.083
What the hell? Give me my phone!

08:48.083 --> 08:49.375
- After dinner.
- Mom!

08:49.375 --> 08:52.250
- I'm not getting in the middle of this.
- Yeah, of course not.

08:53.166 --> 08:55.041
Come on, Frank. Give me a break.

09:06.458 --> 09:10.625
So, what? You'd rather listen
to some old white dude play guitar?

09:12.041 --> 09:14.416
Terry Kath is one of the greatest
guitarists of all time.

09:14.416 --> 09:16.208
"Terry Kath
is one the greatest..."

09:16.208 --> 09:19.250
That's not true.
Jimi Hendrix is the greatest.

09:19.250 --> 09:21.000
Oh. Did you read that in <i>Rolling Stone?</i>

09:21.000 --> 09:23.083
No, it's a fact. Ask anybody.

09:23.083 --> 09:24.875
Or just ask Jimi Hendrix himself.

09:24.875 --> 09:27.541
He said Kath was his greatest inspiration.

09:27.541 --> 09:28.541
He was a genius.

09:28.541 --> 09:31.500
The dude accidentally
shot himself in the face.

09:31.500 --> 09:32.750
A genius he is not.

09:32.750 --> 09:35.833
Says the guy
reading a book for dummies.

09:49.000 --> 09:50.000
You know what?

09:52.375 --> 09:54.208
I'm sorry you're so unhappy.

09:55.458 --> 09:56.458
Okay?

09:56.458 --> 09:59.625
Now, we're all here
trying to get a fresh start.

10:01.333 --> 10:04.291
I'd appreciate it if you'd come at it
with a little bit more positivity.

10:04.875 --> 10:07.000
How many fresh starts are we at now, Dad?

10:08.666 --> 10:09.750
I lost count.

10:28.041 --> 10:28.916
What the hell, man?

10:30.541 --> 10:31.458
What?

10:32.791 --> 10:33.625
He started it.

12:53.583 --> 12:55.166
No, no, no. Wait. Don't go!

12:55.750 --> 12:56.875
Shit.

12:59.833 --> 13:01.291
Holy shit.

13:11.333 --> 13:14.375
"Most entities have been
displaced by trauma."

13:14.375 --> 13:15.416
Psst!

13:16.166 --> 13:17.166
Hey!

13:17.666 --> 13:18.791
Yeah, you.

13:19.375 --> 13:21.250
Can you come in
and guard the door for a sec?

13:21.750 --> 13:22.875
Come on.

13:30.083 --> 13:31.083
Um...

13:32.250 --> 13:34.583
I don't think
you're supposed to be doing that.

13:34.583 --> 13:36.625
Some racist douchebag
wrote my number down.

13:36.625 --> 13:39.541
I keep getting text messages
asking for free rice.

13:39.541 --> 13:40.750
- Free rice?

13:41.416 --> 13:43.666
Oh! You don't know?

13:43.666 --> 13:46.500
Asian people only eat rice.

13:48.041 --> 13:49.291
Why not just change your number?

13:49.291 --> 13:52.000
So, I should cave under the pressure
of institutionalized abuse?

13:52.000 --> 13:52.958
Uh, no. I meant--

13:52.958 --> 13:55.666
Besides, do you know
how clutch this number is?

13:55.666 --> 13:57.250
222-POOP.

13:57.250 --> 14:00.708
Phone numbers that good
are, like, impossible to get.

14:00.708 --> 14:03.666
So, uh, I... I think we're neighbors.

14:03.666 --> 14:04.791
We are?

14:05.291 --> 14:06.541
Yeah. Um...

14:06.541 --> 14:09.041
My family just moved
into the house next to yours.

14:09.041 --> 14:11.166
You moved into the House of Death?

14:12.083 --> 14:14.125
- House of what?
- Everyone says it's haunted.

14:14.125 --> 14:16.958
I'm an atheist, so I'm not
supposed to believe in that kind of shit,

14:16.958 --> 14:20.375
but secretly, I'd love to die
and then, I don't know,

14:20.375 --> 14:23.000
come back as some fierce ghost
and haunt Ted Cruz.

14:24.083 --> 14:25.125
Anyway.

14:25.916 --> 14:30.541
Uh... Neighbor, we should hang.
What are you doing after school?

14:31.333 --> 14:32.791
Oh, um... After school...

14:32.791 --> 14:35.875
Well, I, um...
I have a lot... I have to study.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.791
- That's one thing I have to do, study.
- Cool.

14:38.791 --> 14:43.250
Okay, well, uh, I guess you know my number
in case you change your mind.

14:43.958 --> 14:45.500
Or if you need rice.

15:01.791 --> 15:02.958
Oh, what's with that face?

15:02.958 --> 15:05.041
-  How was your ride home?
- Great.

15:05.041 --> 15:07.125
How about you, Kevin?
How was your ride home?

15:07.125 --> 15:08.041
Good.

15:08.041 --> 15:10.125
- Fulton, give me your phone.
- Why?

15:10.125 --> 15:12.916
Susan said she saw your brother
walk to school this morning.

15:12.916 --> 15:14.708
You had one job.

15:14.708 --> 15:15.958
That's bullshit.

15:15.958 --> 15:16.916
Kevin.

15:17.666 --> 15:18.583
No comment.

15:26.208 --> 15:27.083
Hello?

15:32.833 --> 15:34.125
It's me again.

15:36.208 --> 15:37.041
You there?

15:46.083 --> 15:49.250
<i>♪ Good men through the ages ♪</i>

15:51.000 --> 15:53.500
<i>♪ Trying to find the sun ♪</i>

15:55.541 --> 15:57.541
<i>And I wonder-- ♪</i>

16:15.208 --> 16:16.458
Boo!

16:16.458 --> 16:17.500
Hey. Hey. Stop.

16:18.333 --> 16:19.208
Stop.

16:20.875 --> 16:22.125
It's not happening, bro.

16:23.708 --> 16:26.166
Listen, I know it... it probably worked
on everyone else before,

16:26.166 --> 16:29.708
but my personal life is, like,
1,000 times scarier than this.

16:34.875 --> 16:35.958
Sit down.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.208
Come on.

16:59.583 --> 17:00.708
Cool shirt.

17:01.541 --> 17:05.250
I've only been bowling once
when I was, like, eight.

17:05.875 --> 17:08.541
My dad got into a fistfight
with the guy in the lane next to us

17:08.541 --> 17:10.375
over an order of buffalo wings.

17:11.125 --> 17:13.750
Manager threw my whole family out.
They banned us for life.

17:17.583 --> 17:18.416
Can you talk?

17:21.291 --> 17:23.958
Just moans and groans?

17:28.958 --> 17:31.958
Did you, like, die here?

17:34.208 --> 17:35.041
In this house?

17:38.541 --> 17:39.708
You don't remember?

17:43.458 --> 17:44.791
Do you remember anything?

17:51.791 --> 17:53.083
So,

17:53.875 --> 17:54.916
it's Ernest, right?

17:55.500 --> 17:56.833
The name on your shirt.

18:00.041 --> 18:00.875
I'm Kevin.

18:08.666 --> 18:10.500
- Whoa.

18:12.958 --> 18:13.791
That's so trippy.

18:24.625 --> 18:26.083
Nice to meet you, Ernest.

18:28.875 --> 18:29.750
So...

18:31.708 --> 18:35.500
we can't touch you, but you can touch us?

18:37.875 --> 18:38.791
Hmm.

18:40.083 --> 18:42.208
Kind of like a stripper.

18:44.583 --> 18:45.500
Kev!

18:46.000 --> 18:47.250
I need your phone.

18:47.791 --> 18:49.541
Jeez, it's freezing in here, man.

18:50.875 --> 18:53.333
Yo, butt munch. Your phone, come on.

18:53.333 --> 18:54.583
Why? Why do you need my phone?

18:54.583 --> 18:57.875
Because, unlike you, I have friends.
It's your fault Mom took my phone away.

18:57.875 --> 19:00.208
Um, I didn't drop me
a mile away from school.

19:00.208 --> 19:02.708
- Okay, where is it? Right there? Where?
- No. Fulton.

19:02.708 --> 19:04.291
Stop! Fulton!

19:04.291 --> 19:06.583
Get off of me! Fulton!

19:11.500 --> 19:12.958
What the hell?

19:35.125 --> 19:36.875
Why are you in such a chipper mood?

19:37.666 --> 19:38.500
What?

19:41.333 --> 19:44.041
Am I not allowed
to be in a good mood?

19:44.041 --> 19:46.333
You can be in whatever mood you want.
You know.

19:46.333 --> 19:48.000
Good mood is good. It's just rare.

19:48.000 --> 19:49.833
Hey. Let him have it.

19:51.458 --> 19:52.666
Thank you.

19:53.500 --> 19:54.416
Okay.

19:56.791 --> 19:59.000
<i>We know that every atom,</i>

19:59.000 --> 20:03.833
<i>every molecule of the human body,
is composed of energy,</i>

20:03.833 --> 20:09.666
<i>but what happens to that
human energy field when the body dies?</i>

20:09.666 --> 20:13.583
<i>I believe that
that energy could be captured.</i>

20:13.583 --> 20:16.291
 <i>See the beyond.
Hear the beyond.</i>

20:16.291 --> 20:17.541
<i>Be the beyond.</i>

20:18.250 --> 20:20.916
<i>Judy Romano is the</i> West Bay Medium.

20:20.916 --> 20:23.708
<i>- Friday, 9:00, 8:00 Central on TSE.</i>
-  What the hell is this?

20:25.000 --> 20:26.750
What are you doing with my phone?

20:28.833 --> 20:30.708
- Fulton.
- Oh, you sneaky little bitch.

20:30.708 --> 20:32.208
Why you keeping this shit a secret?

20:32.208 --> 20:33.833
- Fulton, give it to me now!
- Hold on.

20:33.833 --> 20:35.250
Will you two knock it off?

20:35.250 --> 20:36.625
We have a ghost.

20:37.333 --> 20:38.458
- Okay.
- No, I'm serious.

20:38.458 --> 20:40.791
Kevin caught him on camera. Look.

20:41.500 --> 20:43.500
- That some kind of scary movie?
-  No.

20:46.250 --> 20:48.458
Hey, this is pretty good.
How'd you do this?

20:48.458 --> 20:49.666
I didn't do anything.

20:54.458 --> 20:55.666
Oh shit!

20:55.666 --> 20:57.833
- Oh, we gotta show Mom.
- No, no, no, no.

20:57.833 --> 20:59.791
- We can't tell her about this.
- Why not?

20:59.791 --> 21:02.125
Because she'll freak out. You know this.

21:02.875 --> 21:03.833
Come on, pinky swear.

21:08.208 --> 21:10.291
- Seriously?
- Get it up. Come on, pinky swear.

21:12.208 --> 21:13.500
-  Kiss it.
- I'm not gonna--

21:13.500 --> 21:14.583
Kiss it.

21:15.583 --> 21:17.125
- Good.

21:18.083 --> 21:20.791
- Can I have my phone back now?
- Yeah. Send me the video.

21:21.875 --> 21:23.458
- Why?
- Come on!

21:23.458 --> 21:26.791
Why's everything a production with you?
Just send me the video, please?

21:29.083 --> 21:30.291
Fine.

21:31.375 --> 21:32.666
- There.

21:32.666 --> 21:33.875
Got it. Thanks.

21:33.875 --> 21:35.958
Come on.

22:09.541 --> 22:12.416
"The little girl lay there
in quiet terror,

22:12.416 --> 22:14.458
the figure hovering over her bed."

22:14.458 --> 22:17.166
"And though the entity
had no discernible face,

22:17.166 --> 22:20.250
she knew it meant to do her harm."

22:20.250 --> 22:22.750
"In one sudden motion, it launched,

22:22.750 --> 22:25.250
covering her mouth, stopping the scream."

22:25.250 --> 22:27.041
"It smelled of peppermint and rot."

22:27.041 --> 22:27.958
Sh!

22:27.958 --> 22:30.833
"The world started spinning
before she blacked out."

22:31.333 --> 22:34.875
"When she finally awakened,
the entity was gone."

22:35.458 --> 22:37.041
"Of course, no one believed her."

22:37.041 --> 22:38.500
"She was a child."

22:38.500 --> 22:41.916
"It was just a dream.
An overactive imagination."

22:42.750 --> 22:44.625
"But the little girl knew the truth."

22:45.583 --> 22:49.291
"The spirit realm is real,
and it is dangerous."

22:54.916 --> 22:55.875
Thank you.

22:55.875 --> 22:57.916
Nobody believed me either.

22:57.916 --> 22:59.458
My ghost is still with me.

22:59.458 --> 23:02.750
He followed me home
from a Red Lobster six years ago,

23:02.750 --> 23:04.333
and I can't seem to shake him.

23:04.333 --> 23:05.708
Now, I have tried to--

23:05.708 --> 23:09.041
Excuse me! I'm having a conversation here!

23:10.708 --> 23:13.833
He's very possessive and a homosexual.

23:15.083 --> 23:16.375
I am so tired.

23:18.541 --> 23:19.541
Thank you.

23:21.458 --> 23:23.000
Oh God, please.

23:26.291 --> 23:27.416
Hi.

23:27.416 --> 23:29.916
Hey, have you seen that viral video
that's been going around?

23:29.916 --> 23:32.958
I don't do social media.
It makes me nauseous.

23:32.958 --> 23:34.750
Well, guy finds a ghost in his attic.

23:34.750 --> 23:38.083
And I don't know.
I mean, it looks... it looks pretty legit.

23:38.083 --> 23:41.000
They always are until they aren't.

23:46.458 --> 23:48.125
Oh, this... this isn't my book.

23:51.916 --> 23:52.750
Mm.

23:52.750 --> 23:54.083
It has over a thousand views.

23:54.083 --> 23:56.541
- Is that good?
-  Don't quit your day job.

24:02.750 --> 24:05.541
"Cool graphics.
What are you using? Maya or ZBrush?"

24:05.541 --> 24:08.625
"Lame-balls. I've seen better stuff
on <i>Ghost Hunters."</i>

24:08.625 --> 24:10.416
- What?
- They think this is fake.

24:10.416 --> 24:11.625
Yeah, but it's real.

24:13.708 --> 24:16.625
Frank. Are you guys watching dirty stuff?
What are you watching?

24:16.625 --> 24:18.916
- Nothing.
- Dad posted a video of-- Ugh!

24:18.916 --> 24:21.083
- Fulton, I just bought those oranges!
-  God!

24:21.708 --> 24:23.875
Worried about the oranges. Cool.

24:23.875 --> 24:26.333
Organic fruit is expensive.
You guys are up to something.

24:26.333 --> 24:27.541
No, we're not.

24:27.541 --> 24:29.541
- Nothing.
- Hmm. Fishy, fishy.

24:35.958 --> 24:37.083
Snitches get stitches.

24:39.875 --> 24:41.333
- Let's do this.
- Yeah.

25:10.750 --> 25:11.666
Hello?

25:14.041 --> 25:15.458
We don't mean you any harm.

25:16.041 --> 25:18.708
Wikia says you should speak
in a firm, commanding voice

25:18.708 --> 25:20.208
so the ghost knows you're in charge.

25:20.208 --> 25:21.125
Got it.

25:22.333 --> 25:23.916
Spirit of this house!

25:24.541 --> 25:26.000
- Show yourself!
- Yeah.

25:26.000 --> 25:27.291
- Huh?

25:30.541 --> 25:31.500
Dad, look.

25:41.916 --> 25:43.000
Boo.

25:43.000 --> 25:44.500
Oh my gosh.

25:44.500 --> 25:45.583
It's not funny, man.

25:45.583 --> 25:46.958
It's totally funny.

25:46.958 --> 25:48.666
You're gonna scare it away, dumbass.

25:48.666 --> 25:51.750
No. Your patronizing, crappy
exorcist act is scaring it away.

25:55.250 --> 25:56.083
Hey.

25:57.833 --> 25:58.750
It's me again.

25:59.500 --> 26:04.041
This is my... my dad, Frank,
and my brother, Fulton.

26:04.541 --> 26:05.500
What's up?

26:07.750 --> 26:09.041
They wanna meet you.

26:17.250 --> 26:18.250
Lame.

26:18.250 --> 26:19.833
You know what? Hold on.

26:20.500 --> 26:21.458
I have an idea.

26:22.083 --> 26:23.125
Where are you going?

26:23.125 --> 26:24.583
He said he has an idea.

26:25.583 --> 26:27.958
What? He's gonna get the ghost
and bring him back up here?

26:30.416 --> 26:32.416
Oh, look at this fool.

26:32.416 --> 26:33.625
Shut up, dog face.

26:33.625 --> 26:35.750
I actually have a pretty attractive face.
Ask anybody.

26:35.750 --> 26:37.083
Hey. Let him play.

26:51.041 --> 26:54.333
<i>♪ Long as I remember ♪</i>

26:55.375 --> 26:59.208
<i>♪ Oh, the rain's been comin' down ♪</i>

27:00.875 --> 27:04.375
<i>♪ Clouds of mystery pourin' ♪</i>

27:05.458 --> 27:08.791
<i>♪ Confusion on the ground ♪</i>

27:10.500 --> 27:14.375
<i>♪ Good men through the ages ♪</i>

27:14.375 --> 27:16.583
Holy shit, it's working. Keep going.

27:16.583 --> 27:18.541
<i>♪ Trying to find the sun ♪</i>

27:20.125 --> 27:21.791
<i>And I wonder-- ♪</i>

27:23.250 --> 27:25.333
Holy shit, look! There he is. Shit.

27:25.333 --> 27:26.333
Hey.

27:27.000 --> 27:27.875
Hey, it's okay.

27:31.166 --> 27:32.208
All good, see?

27:53.166 --> 27:54.000
Ask him something.

27:55.000 --> 27:56.833
- He can't talk.
- Why not?

27:58.333 --> 27:59.708
I don't know. 'Cause he's a ghost.

28:00.291 --> 28:02.041
-  Frank!
-  Oh shit!

28:02.041 --> 28:03.583
He has to go. Hey, uh...

28:03.583 --> 28:05.708
Beetlejuice, Beetlejuice, Beetlejuice!

28:06.291 --> 28:07.208
 Frank.

28:08.875 --> 28:09.958
What is this?

28:09.958 --> 28:11.500
- Uh...

28:13.625 --> 28:15.958
- Uh--
- Really? Gonna act like we don't know?

28:15.958 --> 28:19.541
Hmm? 'Cause that's our house. Right?

28:22.083 --> 28:23.833
And that's his voice
behind the camera, right?

28:23.833 --> 28:25.750
- I... I, uh--
- You what?

28:25.750 --> 28:28.291
- Uh...
- You what, Frank? What?

28:43.791 --> 28:46.916
26,000 views in less than five minutes.
This is huge.

28:46.916 --> 28:49.708
- I saw it with my own eyes, Barbara.

28:49.708 --> 28:52.083
<i>Sweetie, I'm sure you think you did.</i>

28:52.083 --> 28:54.833
<i>My daughter Carly took a Xanax
with a bottle of Pinot Grigio</i>

28:54.833 --> 28:56.166
<i>and thought she was Edith Piaf.</i>

28:56.166 --> 28:59.125
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
I'm not on drugs. We have proof.

28:59.125 --> 29:01.083
There's footage online.

29:01.083 --> 29:03.625
- Hey, where do you think you're going?
- Out?

29:03.625 --> 29:05.375
- Uh, no. Not so fast.
- Mom!

29:05.375 --> 29:08.541
Barbara, I'm pretty sure you broke
some kind of non-disclosure laws here.

29:08.541 --> 29:11.291
<i>We don't have to disclose ghosts.
Not in the fine print.</i>

29:11.291 --> 29:14.083
Oh! Well, then you'll be hearing
from our lawyer.

29:14.083 --> 29:16.250
- We have a lawyer?
- Of course not. We're broke.

29:16.250 --> 29:18.083
- 27,000!
- Can I go?

29:18.083 --> 29:20.291
No! You were in on this whole thing!

29:20.291 --> 29:22.041
Dad made us promise.

29:22.041 --> 29:22.958
Oh my God. Frank.

29:22.958 --> 29:24.958
- I knew you were gonna freak out.
- Yes!

29:24.958 --> 29:27.666
Any rational human being would!

29:27.666 --> 29:30.083
We have a ghost in our attic!

29:30.083 --> 29:32.875
- Mel, I'm sorry. I should've--
- And then to hear it from someone else?

29:32.875 --> 29:37.208
Somebody who saw it on freaking YouTube?
What happened to communicating more?

29:37.791 --> 29:41.208
Wasn't that the point of sitting through
20 sessions with Dr. Mouth-breather?

29:41.208 --> 29:43.458
- Okay. I'm out.
- Kevin.

29:43.458 --> 29:46.083
30,000. I'm so getting laid for this.

29:46.083 --> 29:48.333
- Fulton!
- Get out of here.

29:53.416 --> 29:54.250
Mel, I'm sorry.

29:54.833 --> 29:57.166
- We are moving.
- No. Wait, no. No, no, no.

29:57.166 --> 29:58.791
- Wait, wait, wait.
- No. No, no, no, no.

29:58.791 --> 29:59.833
We are not gonna be like

29:59.833 --> 30:04.208
every stupid white family
in every horror film. We are leaving.

30:04.208 --> 30:06.375
Will you just hear me out? Please, listen.

30:08.083 --> 30:08.958
Mel.

30:11.083 --> 30:13.208
I don't think
you understand how big this is.

30:13.916 --> 30:17.666
We've captured something
no one else ever has, ever,

30:17.666 --> 30:19.541
in the history of the recorded world!

30:19.541 --> 30:21.166
This is not up for discussion, Frank!

30:21.166 --> 30:23.291
Okay. So who are you
gonna sell the house to, huh?

30:23.291 --> 30:26.375
Because every dollar we have
is wrapped up into this.

30:26.375 --> 30:28.500
Well, if it wasn't for you
and that stupid video--

30:28.500 --> 30:29.541
And that's my point.

30:31.000 --> 30:32.208
That's money, baby.

30:32.875 --> 30:36.708
Look, you have guys out there right now
making millions on their channel

30:36.708 --> 30:40.750
by playing <i>Minecraft</i>
and lighting their farts on fire!

30:40.750 --> 30:43.208
And, Mel, we actually have a ghost!

30:47.375 --> 30:48.500
This feels like Houston.

30:49.750 --> 30:51.916
Houston was a pyramid scheme.
That's different.

30:51.916 --> 30:53.375
This... this is real.

30:54.208 --> 30:57.125
This is our chance.
This could change everything.

30:59.625 --> 31:00.791
Mel.

31:02.500 --> 31:04.166
Look at me, baby. Please?

31:07.000 --> 31:08.000
Look.

31:11.333 --> 31:14.291
I just need to win once.

31:15.916 --> 31:17.000
Just once.

31:21.125 --> 31:22.625
You know this is crazy.

31:23.125 --> 31:24.000
Right?

31:33.958 --> 31:35.833
<i>-That's not a ghost.
- Are you kidding me?</i>

31:35.833 --> 31:37.166
<i>He just walked through the wall!</i>

31:40.708 --> 31:41.750
<i>Oh Jesus!</i>

31:41.750 --> 31:43.083
<i>- Nuh-uh!</i>

31:43.083 --> 31:44.208
<i>What is this?</i>

31:59.791 --> 32:02.375
<i>Ernest is fine!</i>

32:02.375 --> 32:03.291
<i>Mmm!</i>

32:03.291 --> 32:05.916
<i>I do have a crush
on Ernest the ghost!</i>

32:05.916 --> 32:09.083
<i>I had a dream last night
that Ernie impregnated me.</i>

32:09.083 --> 32:10.541
<i>This is what our son looked like.</i>

32:10.541 --> 32:12.750
<i>"Run into a wall like Ernest."</i>

32:13.708 --> 32:15.625
<i>Oh my gosh. Okay.</i>

32:19.125 --> 32:21.833
<i>-You good? You good... Dude, your face.</i>

32:21.833 --> 32:25.166
<i>My name's Cory, and we're going
with the Ernest Challenge. Check me out.</i>

32:32.375 --> 32:34.666
<i>Ghost rights are human rights, you guys.</i>

32:34.666 --> 32:36.125
<i>Ghost rights.</i>

32:36.666 --> 32:38.000
<i>What?</i>

32:38.000 --> 32:42.208
<i>Just because you're not made of matter,
it doesn't mean you don't matter.</i>

32:42.208 --> 32:44.041
<i>If you want rights, go to New Zealand.</i>

32:44.041 --> 32:46.958
<i>They'd love to have you,
but we're fine. Thank you very much.</i>

32:46.958 --> 32:48.666
<i>Also, COVID is not real.</i>

32:48.666 --> 32:49.666
<i>Mental abuse!</i>

32:49.666 --> 32:51.916
<i>I'm just out here
trying to normalize ghost love.</i>

32:51.916 --> 32:54.750
<i>-They're among us.
- Light one up for my ghoulies.</i>

32:54.750 --> 32:57.625
<i>-Who knew someone so dark...
- He's just living in the house.</i>

32:57.625 --> 32:59.333
<i>...could make me feel...</i>

33:13.416 --> 33:16.000
<i>It's a classic campfire tale.</i>

33:16.000 --> 33:20.250
<i>A family moves into an old house
that has a ghost lurking in its halls.</i>

33:20.250 --> 33:24.458
<i>But for a family in Chicago,
that spooky scenario just became real,</i>

33:24.458 --> 33:28.250
<i>and they've got the YouTube videos
to prove it. Take a look.</i>

33:28.250 --> 33:29.416
<i>Frank.</i>

33:31.500 --> 33:33.291
<i>- What is this?</i>
-  <i>Uh...</i>

33:33.291 --> 33:34.208
<i>What?</i>

33:37.166 --> 33:39.541
<i>- It might be time to call the movers.</i>

33:40.666 --> 33:44.083
-  <i>My guests today have...</i>
- Holy shit.

33:45.666 --> 33:49.416
Make sure Anderson gets briefed
before we meet with Congressional Affairs.

33:49.416 --> 33:52.041
Are you chewing gum?
What else we got?

33:52.041 --> 33:54.833
- That woman called again. Leslie?
-  Agent Schipley!

33:54.833 --> 33:57.250
- Oh, Christ on a cracker.
<i>-</i> Agent Schipley.

33:57.250 --> 33:58.958
Leslie. What a lovely surprise.

33:58.958 --> 34:01.458
I've been calling your office
for the past three days.

34:01.458 --> 34:03.541
- Really? I didn't know.
- You saw this, right?

34:04.083 --> 34:05.791
- Uh, no clue.
- It's an RHE.

34:05.791 --> 34:09.208
Leslie, I really appreciate you coming
all the way down here, but--

34:09.208 --> 34:12.375
I ran prelim diagnostics.
I couldn't find any foreign artifacts.

34:13.291 --> 34:16.208
Digital forensics, clean. This one's real.

34:16.208 --> 34:18.041
We need to reopen Wizard Clip.

34:18.041 --> 34:21.500
That program was mothballed 20 years ago
and for a good reason.

34:21.500 --> 34:23.958
This is our chance
to prove once and for all

34:23.958 --> 34:26.625
that spectral phenomena
is not some fantasy.

34:26.625 --> 34:27.791
Let's go.

34:29.125 --> 34:31.125
- Thanks for coming down.
- Please! He's real!

34:31.125 --> 34:34.416
- Come with us, ma'am. Come on, ma'am.
- He's real! Agent Schipley!

34:35.041 --> 34:36.916
He's real! Please!

34:39.833 --> 34:40.958
What?

34:42.583 --> 34:45.916
This is crazy.
How you doing? Yo! What's up?

34:48.500 --> 34:49.958
This is insane.

34:51.000 --> 34:53.250
Yo, what's up?
What's up? What's up?

34:55.791 --> 34:57.458
How do you feel about this ghost?

34:59.000 --> 35:00.875
Can you tell us more about Ernest?

35:00.875 --> 35:04.791
Yo, one second! One second!
Okay, all right! Yo!

35:04.791 --> 35:07.583
Frank, please.
Frank, tell us, please, about the entity!

35:07.583 --> 35:09.833
- All right, okay, yeah.
- The supernatural entity, Ernest!

35:09.833 --> 35:11.666
When's the last time you saw Ernie?

35:12.833 --> 35:15.333
How do you respond
to those who say this is all a hoax?

35:15.333 --> 35:17.166
Uh, if you think it's a hoax, look around.

35:17.166 --> 35:19.583
- There's a lot of people here. I mean...
- Is your family safe?

35:19.583 --> 35:21.458
- Is the community safe?
- When's the last time...

35:21.458 --> 35:23.791
Of course they're safe.
I mean, he's a ghost.

35:25.458 --> 35:27.208
Hey, thank you, guys!

35:31.791 --> 35:34.458
Who is coming into my house?

35:34.458 --> 35:37.708
You guys have a lot of nerve!
This is a private re...

35:37.708 --> 35:38.916
Frank!

35:38.916 --> 35:40.458
- I know.
- This is insane.

35:40.458 --> 35:41.958
- I can't leave the house.

35:41.958 --> 35:43.083
It's not that bad.

35:43.083 --> 35:44.583
Whoa, not that bad?

35:44.583 --> 35:46.541
Someone tried
to crawl down the chimney today...

35:46.541 --> 35:49.250
- What?
- ...to get in. Yeah! They got stuck.

35:49.250 --> 35:51.791
- I had to call the fire department.

35:51.791 --> 35:54.666
Do you know how crazy that is
to have a human being in there?

35:54.666 --> 35:56.250
- It ain't Christm--

35:57.625 --> 35:58.791
- Jesus Christ.
- Ha!

35:58.791 --> 36:00.375
- Not funny.
- Oh...

36:00.375 --> 36:03.666
Hey, go away, or we're calling the cops.

36:05.666 --> 36:10.750
Everything I've read says that
memory loss is connected to trauma.

36:11.500 --> 36:13.000
It's a self-defense mechanism.

36:14.166 --> 36:17.791
We need visual stimuli
to help trigger your memory.

36:19.583 --> 36:20.541
Oh my God.

36:22.333 --> 36:23.208
No?

36:24.791 --> 36:25.875
It's creepy.

36:30.250 --> 36:33.625
It's one of Dad's failed business things.

36:33.625 --> 36:34.875
"Male enhancement pills."

36:34.875 --> 36:37.791
But instead of boners,
they just gave everyone diarrhea.

36:46.333 --> 36:47.416
Do you remember something?

36:53.291 --> 36:54.250
Okay. Okay.

36:54.250 --> 36:55.458
It's okay.

37:06.208 --> 37:07.583
Move out, move.

37:12.666 --> 37:14.833
- You know, there's ghosts everywhere!
- Look at him.

37:16.708 --> 37:17.833
He loves it.

37:19.083 --> 37:19.916
Wh...

37:26.083 --> 37:28.125
Why help?

37:28.708 --> 37:30.125
"Why"? Why, what?

37:42.791 --> 37:44.333
Why help you?

37:46.833 --> 37:48.083
'Cause you're stuck.

37:50.250 --> 37:52.375
Nobody wants to be stuck, right?

38:02.541 --> 38:03.958
- Hey, neighbor!

38:05.000 --> 38:06.000
That...

38:06.583 --> 38:07.583
That was loud.

38:07.583 --> 38:10.000
I've never understood
the whole "quiet-in-the-library" thing.

38:10.000 --> 38:13.125
Like, what?
Noise makes you stupid?

38:13.125 --> 38:15.083
Anyway, how are you? How's the ghost?

38:15.666 --> 38:17.791
Our whole street's a shitshow,
thanks to you guys.

38:17.791 --> 38:20.208
My dad has the tow company on speed dial.

38:20.708 --> 38:22.083
It's kind of bad, actually.

38:22.083 --> 38:23.041
Oh.

38:24.166 --> 38:25.416
- Sorry.

38:27.333 --> 38:28.541
What are you working on?

38:29.083 --> 38:29.958
Uh...

38:29.958 --> 38:31.416
Ooh. Property records?

38:31.416 --> 38:32.541
Uh, yeah.

38:32.541 --> 38:36.250
I'm trying to see if Ernest
actually lived in our house

38:36.250 --> 38:37.166
before he died.

38:37.166 --> 38:40.625
- He doesn't remember how he got there?
- He doesn't remember anything.

38:40.625 --> 38:42.250
Ooh. A mystery.

38:43.041 --> 38:44.666
Yeah, I'm just-- Oh.

38:45.250 --> 38:47.000
- Okay.

38:48.291 --> 38:49.750
Are you, like, a hacker or something?

38:52.958 --> 38:54.625
Ta-da! Mystery solved.

38:55.208 --> 38:56.208
Ernest Scheller.

38:56.208 --> 38:58.875
Bought the house April 5th, 1965,

38:58.875 --> 39:01.416
and sold it December 15th, 1971.

39:01.416 --> 39:03.166
- How did he die?
- Gimme a sec.

39:06.041 --> 39:08.333
Oh. Weird. There's no death certificate.

39:08.916 --> 39:10.583
- Pretty sure he's dead.
- You think?

39:13.041 --> 39:16.291
Sorry.
Looks like a dead end. Puns!

39:17.208 --> 39:19.875
Uh, I gotta run.
Band practice. But good luck.

39:20.875 --> 39:21.750
Thanks.

39:32.333 --> 39:34.375
-  Tina, here.

39:46.458 --> 39:49.500
I... I don't wanna hurt your feelings
or anything, but I... I'm drawing the line.

39:49.500 --> 39:52.000
No more rest home readings.

39:52.000 --> 39:53.916
The food always sucks.

39:53.916 --> 39:58.208
What about Kris Jenner? Doesn't she have
someone in her family that died recently?

39:58.875 --> 40:00.458
Her dog? I'm not--

40:00.458 --> 40:02.291
- Oh. Hey. Hi.
-  Hey.

40:02.291 --> 40:04.083
You know, I just... I gotta go. I gotta go.

40:04.083 --> 40:06.541
All right. Okay.
Okay, okay. I gotta go. Hey.

40:06.541 --> 40:09.291
- Hey! Hello. Hey!
- Hey.

40:09.291 --> 40:10.750
Oh my gosh.

40:11.333 --> 40:13.333
- You must be Frank.
-  Yeah.

40:13.333 --> 40:17.375
Everyone here at TSC is just thrilled
about you and everything happening.

40:17.375 --> 40:20.416
Well, we're really excited
to have you in our home.

40:20.416 --> 40:22.291
We're huge fans of the show.

40:22.291 --> 40:24.125
- Aw.
- We watch the show all the time.

40:24.125 --> 40:26.166
You're a gem.
You're a gem. You really are.

40:27.541 --> 40:30.208
Oh, and you're cute!

40:30.791 --> 40:32.833
Nobody said you were cute!

40:33.458 --> 40:34.291
Nobody.

40:34.291 --> 40:36.250
- Just wanna know, where's the wifey?

40:36.250 --> 40:38.125
Uh, she's somewhere getting ready.

40:38.125 --> 40:39.125
Good.

40:39.875 --> 40:40.916
Lock her up.

40:41.833 --> 40:44.875
That's right. And put her in a box
under the bed because

40:44.875 --> 40:46.166
you're mine.

40:51.583 --> 40:54.041
Well, can you make sure that

40:54.041 --> 40:56.166
"he's" ready for me?

40:57.291 --> 40:58.458
- Ernest!
- Yes!

40:58.458 --> 41:00.791
He's... he's good to go. We're ready. We...

41:00.791 --> 41:02.333
- We're cool.
-  Oh, good.

41:03.416 --> 41:05.375
Because I'm ready for him.

41:10.666 --> 41:12.208
Oh. Look, look. See?

41:14.875 --> 41:16.791
That's the kind of vibe you gotta work.

41:16.791 --> 41:18.708
Intensity. Visceral.

41:21.666 --> 41:23.500
- Where'd he go? Make him come back.
- Who?

41:23.500 --> 41:25.541
Kevin, don't play around.
I know he was here.

41:25.541 --> 41:26.833
He's not your lapdog.

41:26.833 --> 41:28.208
I didn't say he--

41:28.208 --> 41:30.791
Look, I got Judy Romano
in my living room right now, man.

41:30.791 --> 41:34.125
- I don't even know who that is.
- Yo, the West Bay Medium's downstairs!

41:34.125 --> 41:35.208
That's who it is!

41:36.916 --> 41:38.375
Why can't you just ask him yourself?

41:38.375 --> 41:39.625
Because he likes you.

41:39.625 --> 41:41.291
- He listens to you.

41:41.291 --> 41:43.875
Sorry to interrupt,
but we're ready for you downstairs.

41:43.875 --> 41:46.000
I'm so sorry. Thank you for your patience.

41:46.000 --> 41:47.416
We'll be right down.

41:50.083 --> 41:52.500
Look, this is important, okay?

41:52.500 --> 41:55.583
Now, this show has a huge following.

41:55.583 --> 41:56.916
Now, if we nail this,

41:56.916 --> 41:59.916
I'm talking about book deals, merchandising...

41:59.916 --> 42:03.208
We could be the Black Kardashians.
Don't you wanna be Kim Kardashian?

42:08.291 --> 42:09.958
Okay.

42:10.750 --> 42:11.583
Anyway.

42:13.416 --> 42:15.041
- Fine.
- You'll talk to him?

42:15.041 --> 42:16.166
I'll try.

42:16.833 --> 42:18.750
My man.

42:23.750 --> 42:24.750
Hey, Ernest.

42:27.208 --> 42:28.375
Ready to have some fun?

42:33.166 --> 42:34.041
Are we rolling?

42:34.041 --> 42:35.041
Oh!

42:39.166 --> 42:40.083
There.

42:41.041 --> 42:42.916
- Oh. So, Frank.

42:42.916 --> 42:49.000
The entire world right now is captivated
by your interactions with Ernest.

42:49.000 --> 42:49.916
Yeah.

42:49.916 --> 42:53.458
You know, but there's
a fair amount of skepticism out there too.

42:53.458 --> 42:55.416
I mean, even myself. Even myself.

42:55.416 --> 42:56.333
I was like,

42:56.833 --> 42:59.333
"I don't think I believe
these videotapes," you know?

42:59.333 --> 43:03.916
But now that I am here,
right in this room,

43:03.916 --> 43:05.791
feeling what I'm feeling,

43:06.500 --> 43:09.875
I mean...
...it's all very palpable, isn't it, right?

43:09.875 --> 43:12.041
Yeah. Ernest is real.

43:12.041 --> 43:14.375
There's... there's no magic here.

43:14.375 --> 43:17.541
So... is he here now?

43:17.541 --> 43:21.750
He... he... he's coming. Right?

43:21.750 --> 43:24.708
He's just shy, you know?
There's a lot of... a lot of people.

43:24.708 --> 43:25.875
Uh-huh.

43:31.500 --> 43:32.500
Frank.

43:33.666 --> 43:35.708
Oh. Oh. Um...

43:36.333 --> 43:37.166
Uh...

43:38.208 --> 43:39.291
Ernest!

43:40.750 --> 43:41.791
You here, man?

43:45.000 --> 43:47.916
-  Ernest, everyone's waiting.

43:47.916 --> 43:48.833
No.

43:48.833 --> 43:51.291
Okay. Okay.

43:51.291 --> 43:53.291
Listen, Frank, if you could just, uh,

43:53.291 --> 43:56.541
fix your little hologram machine, okay,
'cause I need to get outta here.

43:56.541 --> 44:00.166
No, no, no. There is no hologram.
He's...

44:01.666 --> 44:02.750
Ernest!

44:02.750 --> 44:04.375
- We're outta here.
- No, wait.

44:04.375 --> 44:06.458
-  We're done.
-  Stop, no. Stop, please.

44:06.458 --> 44:08.041
Just... just wait, please?

44:45.750 --> 44:46.750
Hey.

44:47.333 --> 44:48.750
Great production value, Frank.

44:49.458 --> 44:51.083
- What?

45:28.916 --> 45:30.750
- Do something!

45:30.750 --> 45:32.625
- What am I supposed to do?
- Tell him to stop!

45:32.625 --> 45:33.791
Oh God!

45:34.833 --> 45:37.083
I gotta get out of basic cable.

45:37.083 --> 45:38.791
It's just so unprofesh.

45:53.875 --> 45:55.833
What the...

46:07.250 --> 46:09.416
Oh. You again.

46:14.208 --> 46:18.541
Yeah, you know what?
On second thought, Tupac was better.

46:18.541 --> 46:20.666
Yeah. I'm gonna have to fix you in post.

46:58.500 --> 46:59.875
This is a disaster.

47:00.458 --> 47:02.208
They wanted a ghost. They got a ghost.

47:02.208 --> 47:04.625
Yeah, they wanted a ghost,
and we gave 'em <i>The Conjuring</i>.

47:05.625 --> 47:07.875
Oh, it's funny to you, huh?
Everything's a joke to you.

