- Don't make me repeat myself now.

1:07:33.625 --> 1:07:34.875
Really sorry about this!

1:07:35.958 --> 1:07:37.750
You have anything on you... Freeze!

1:07:46.458 --> 1:07:47.666
Don't move!

1:07:47.666 --> 1:07:48.916
Ha... Hands up!

1:07:54.250 --> 1:07:56.458
- Go, go, go, go, go.

1:07:57.750 --> 1:08:00.958
- Oh my God. I kicked him in the nuts!

1:08:00.958 --> 1:08:02.541
- Where's Ernest?
- I don't know!

1:08:09.208 --> 1:08:10.791
- Hey, stop!
- Go, go, go, go, go!

1:08:13.791 --> 1:08:15.125
What in the hell are you doing?

1:08:15.125 --> 1:08:17.208
- He just flipped me off!
<i>-</i> Move your dumb ass!

1:08:28.291 --> 1:08:29.250
Shit.

1:08:31.125 --> 1:08:32.583
I think we lost them.

1:08:33.708 --> 1:08:35.666
- Oh shit!
- Shit!

1:08:35.666 --> 1:08:37.541
<i>♪ Nobody gonna take my car ♪</i>

1:08:37.541 --> 1:08:40.875
<i>♪ I'm gonna race it to the ground... ♪</i>

1:08:40.875 --> 1:08:42.250
He's right behind us, Kevin!

1:08:43.875 --> 1:08:46.333
- You got eyes on him yet?
- Oh shit. This is really happening.

1:08:46.333 --> 1:08:47.250
There! Turn there!

1:08:47.250 --> 1:08:49.041
<i>♪ Ooh, it's a killing machine ♪</i>

1:08:49.666 --> 1:08:51.625
<i>♪ It's got everything ♪</i>

1:08:51.625 --> 1:08:54.500
I've got him!
Cut him off on the other side! Yeah!

1:08:54.500 --> 1:08:57.375
<i>♪ Big fat tires and everything... ♪</i>

1:09:00.791 --> 1:09:02.041
Shit, shit, shit, shit!

1:09:07.291 --> 1:09:08.333
God! They're everywhere!

1:09:08.333 --> 1:09:10.541
- Will they let us off if we pull over?
- Are you crazy?

1:09:11.916 --> 1:09:14.041
<i>♪ Nobody gonna take my girl... ♪</i>

1:09:14.833 --> 1:09:16.833
Kicked me in my nuts, hit my car!

1:09:17.458 --> 1:09:19.458
<i>♪ Ooh, she's a killing machine ♪</i>

1:09:20.333 --> 1:09:21.750
<i>♪ She's got everything... ♪</i>

1:09:23.041 --> 1:09:24.416
Oh shit!

1:09:25.375 --> 1:09:26.875
Let go!

1:09:41.125 --> 1:09:42.625
- Kevin!
- I see him!

1:09:42.625 --> 1:09:44.500
You wanna play chicken? Come on!

1:09:52.041 --> 1:09:53.791
- Welcome back.

1:09:53.791 --> 1:09:54.750
You son of a...

1:09:55.833 --> 1:09:57.000
The other one's coming.

1:09:59.208 --> 1:10:00.416
Oh, oh...

1:10:11.666 --> 1:10:13.041
Oh shit!

1:10:31.375 --> 1:10:33.041
Holy shit, Ernest. What are you doing?

1:10:49.041 --> 1:10:50.333
- Kevin, stop!
- I can make it!

1:10:50.333 --> 1:10:51.791
No, you can't! Stop! Kevin!

1:10:54.791 --> 1:10:56.375
- Oh shit!

1:11:07.041 --> 1:11:08.125
Oh shit!

1:11:18.416 --> 1:11:20.083
Never do that again.

1:11:21.291 --> 1:11:22.125
Yeah.

1:11:22.708 --> 1:11:24.166
Get your ass back here!

1:11:27.000 --> 1:11:28.208
Shit!

1:11:35.250 --> 1:11:36.375
Where's he going?

1:11:37.000 --> 1:11:39.916
We already told you. We don't know.

1:11:39.916 --> 1:11:42.208
We have a right
to legal counsel, all right?

1:11:42.208 --> 1:11:43.958
You can't hold us here like animals.

1:11:43.958 --> 1:11:46.041
When can I get my phone back?

1:11:47.208 --> 1:11:49.208
You know what?
I've gotta go to the restroom.

1:11:53.625 --> 1:11:55.625
Do I need permission to pee?

1:11:57.333 --> 1:11:58.375
Let her go.

1:12:10.041 --> 1:12:12.833
Oh my goodness!
I am so sorry! Are you okay?

1:12:12.833 --> 1:12:14.416
Oh my God.

1:12:20.458 --> 1:12:21.291
Hello?

1:12:21.291 --> 1:12:22.333
Mom.

1:12:22.333 --> 1:12:24.541
Oh my God, Kevin. Are you okay?

1:12:24.541 --> 1:12:26.125
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

1:12:26.125 --> 1:12:27.250
<i>Where are you?</i>

1:12:28.583 --> 1:12:31.583
I can't tell you, I'm sorry.
But I'm safe. I promise.

1:12:31.583 --> 1:12:34.000
<i>I think we might have found someone
who can help Ernest.</i>

1:12:34.000 --> 1:12:37.125
Okay. Listen to me. Just keep going.

1:12:37.125 --> 1:12:39.791
<i>You do whatever
your heart tells you is right.</i>

1:12:39.791 --> 1:12:41.791
I love you so much. Okay.

1:12:41.791 --> 1:12:42.875
<i>I love you too.</i>

1:12:44.750 --> 1:12:47.250
Those darn telemarketers.
They're the worst, right?

1:12:48.291 --> 1:12:52.250
Aiding and abetting
a known fugitive is a federal crime.

1:12:52.250 --> 1:12:53.625
Where is he?

1:12:54.875 --> 1:12:59.125
Lady, I'd just as soon
swallow a bag of razor blades

1:12:59.125 --> 1:13:03.625
and chase it with some fresh lemon juice
than to tell you jack shit.

1:13:04.833 --> 1:13:06.958
Ma'am, there's someone you should talk to.

1:13:27.958 --> 1:13:30.083
<i>The car,
with Ernest the ghost inside,</i>

1:13:30.083 --> 1:13:33.125
<i>sped through the town
in an attempt to evade authorities,</i>

1:13:33.125 --> 1:13:35.416
<i>causing damage all along the strip...</i>

1:13:59.375 --> 1:14:00.375
What are you doing?

1:14:00.375 --> 1:14:03.041
Looking for the dead body.
This room reeks.

1:14:11.750 --> 1:14:12.583
Rusty.

1:14:26.833 --> 1:14:27.958
Oh my God.

1:14:28.958 --> 1:14:30.583
Wait, this must be a mistake.

1:14:32.291 --> 1:14:35.083
- Maybe I should take a dump on the bed.

1:14:36.000 --> 1:14:37.666
We could just share this one.

1:14:38.500 --> 1:14:39.333
Sh... Share?

1:14:39.916 --> 1:14:41.750
Just don't try to dry hump me.

1:14:42.708 --> 1:14:45.000
Oh! No, I... I would never... I... I...

1:14:45.000 --> 1:14:45.916
I'm kidding.

1:14:46.750 --> 1:14:48.125
Come here. Grab the remote.

1:14:57.875 --> 1:15:00.791
<i>♪ Lonely rivers sigh ♪</i>

1:15:00.791 --> 1:15:04.208
<i>♪ "Wait for me, wait for me" ♪</i>

1:15:05.083 --> 1:15:06.208
<i>♪ I'll-- ♪</i>

1:15:06.208 --> 1:15:08.458
<i>The global outcry continues</i>

1:15:08.458 --> 1:15:11.666
<i>with protests
demanding the ethical treatment of Ernest.</i>

1:15:11.666 --> 1:15:13.791
-  <i>I'd like to solve the puzzle!</i>
-  <i>Go ahead.</i>

1:15:13.791 --> 1:15:15.750
-  <i>Ernest the ghost.</i>
-  <i>Yeah.</i>

1:15:17.750 --> 1:15:18.750
Wow.

1:15:19.416 --> 1:15:21.250
This is really a thing, huh?

1:15:23.375 --> 1:15:25.291
<i>Wow. Look at this.</i>

1:15:25.291 --> 1:15:28.416
Look, it's not too late
for you to get out of this.

1:15:28.416 --> 1:15:29.375
What?

1:15:30.375 --> 1:15:32.375
I mean, everyone thinks you're kidnapped.

1:15:33.083 --> 1:15:35.708
You could just pretend you got away.

1:15:36.750 --> 1:15:37.791
Wait.

1:15:39.541 --> 1:15:41.375
You're saying I should just ditch you?

1:15:42.041 --> 1:15:44.416
- Why would I do that?
- So you don't go to jail, maybe?

1:15:45.375 --> 1:15:46.791
It's a good reason.

1:15:46.791 --> 1:15:48.041
Are you kidding?

1:15:48.750 --> 1:15:49.791
I was already in jail.

1:15:50.833 --> 1:15:54.500
Band, AP classes,
math tutoring, choir practice.

1:15:55.250 --> 1:15:59.041
My dad's programmed every second
of my life, and it's exhausting.

1:15:59.041 --> 1:16:01.250
At least your dad cares.

1:16:02.083 --> 1:16:03.291
It's a culture thing.

1:16:03.958 --> 1:16:05.541
We have to be the best.

1:16:06.250 --> 1:16:08.875
Prove that we belong. It's bullshit.

1:16:09.708 --> 1:16:12.791
Sometimes it just seems
like he doesn't even know me.

1:16:14.125 --> 1:16:17.041
He just sees this fake version of me
that he created.

1:16:17.041 --> 1:16:20.041
I don't know.
I guess it's what a lot of parents do.

1:16:20.875 --> 1:16:25.708
Try and fix themselves through their kids,
but they just mess 'em up more in the end.

1:16:27.208 --> 1:16:31.833
The sad thing is me and my dad were
actually best friends when I was a kid.

1:16:33.708 --> 1:16:34.708
I miss that.

1:16:36.291 --> 1:16:37.125
What happened?

1:16:37.958 --> 1:16:39.833
I don't know. It...

1:16:41.083 --> 1:16:45.916
It wasn't just one thing. It was, like,
a bunch of things over time, and...

1:16:47.625 --> 1:16:48.708
us moving around a lot,

1:16:49.333 --> 1:16:53.541
him promising things to my mom
that just never happened.

1:16:55.208 --> 1:16:56.875
Seeing how much it would hurt her.

1:16:57.708 --> 1:16:59.583
After a while, I just pulled away.

1:17:01.875 --> 1:17:04.375
Sometimes I feel like
I'm not even his son anymore.

1:17:16.083 --> 1:17:17.000
What?

1:17:18.791 --> 1:17:19.708
You're just...

1:17:21.291 --> 1:17:22.583
You're really cool.

1:17:25.333 --> 1:17:26.500
Thank you for helping us.

1:17:31.041 --> 1:17:32.875
<i>♪ My darling, I ♪</i>

1:17:34.541 --> 1:17:36.791
<i>♪ Can't get enough of your love, babe... ♪</i>

1:17:37.583 --> 1:17:39.500
I have to go
to the restroom.

1:17:39.500 --> 1:17:40.750
- Okay.
- Just one sec.

1:17:40.750 --> 1:17:41.666
Yeah.

1:17:43.208 --> 1:17:45.666
<i>♪ I can't get enough of your love, babe ♪</i>

1:17:46.416 --> 1:17:47.291
Ernest.

1:17:50.500 --> 1:17:51.583
Would you knock it off?

1:17:52.166 --> 1:17:53.583
Ernest, stop.

1:17:53.583 --> 1:17:55.416
Ernest. Listen to me.

1:17:55.416 --> 1:17:57.916
- What are you doing? Stop, Ernest.

1:18:00.666 --> 1:18:02.541
- What? What is this?
- Ah!

1:18:03.083 --> 1:18:03.916
What?

1:18:04.958 --> 1:18:05.875
Stop. Ernest!

1:18:07.583 --> 1:18:09.750
- Everything okay?
- Yeah.

1:18:09.750 --> 1:18:11.000
Yeah. [clears throat] Yeah.

1:18:11.000 --> 1:18:13.541
Uh, everything's fine.

1:18:46.625 --> 1:18:48.125
Go away.

1:19:23.291 --> 1:19:24.208
I'll stay here.

1:19:25.083 --> 1:19:26.083
Keep a lookout.

1:19:27.916 --> 1:19:30.125
Honk the horn
if you see anything suspicious.

1:19:31.916 --> 1:19:33.250
Stay out of sight, okay?

1:20:10.291 --> 1:20:11.250
Hi.

1:20:12.500 --> 1:20:14.083
Are you Ernest Scheller?

1:20:15.750 --> 1:20:17.958
- I'm--
- I know who you are. Come in.

1:20:26.625 --> 1:20:28.500
That's my wife, Ramona.

1:20:30.166 --> 1:20:32.833
Suffered a stroke last year.

1:20:32.833 --> 1:20:35.000
Can't really do much these days.

1:20:37.333 --> 1:20:38.500
Have a seat.

1:20:44.791 --> 1:20:47.291
Can I get you something to drink?

1:20:47.291 --> 1:20:51.083
Um, juice, pop, pineapple juice?

1:20:51.083 --> 1:20:53.750
Ramona loves pineapple juice.

1:20:54.375 --> 1:20:55.500
Whatever you want.

1:20:55.500 --> 1:20:57.666
No, no. No, I'm fine.

1:20:58.458 --> 1:20:59.500
Okay.

1:21:03.000 --> 1:21:04.625
Funny thing, I, uh...

1:21:06.666 --> 1:21:10.666
I was in a bowling league ages ago.

1:21:12.250 --> 1:21:14.583
One day, I can't find my shirt.

1:21:15.291 --> 1:21:16.916
I looked high and low.

1:21:17.958 --> 1:21:21.083
Ramona said I was always losing things,

1:21:21.083 --> 1:21:24.916
even the damn shirt
off my own back, but, uh...

1:21:26.750 --> 1:21:28.625
I knew something wasn't right.

1:21:31.750 --> 1:21:33.791
I didn't see that shirt again

1:21:33.791 --> 1:21:38.333
till a couple of weeks ago
when I saw one of your videos on the TV.

1:21:40.041 --> 1:21:44.166
Well, I've seen
some crazy things in my life, but this...

1:21:46.333 --> 1:21:49.166
I really can't believe this is real.

1:21:54.875 --> 1:21:57.958
His name was Randy. Randy McGovern.

1:21:57.958 --> 1:22:01.958
That woman next to him
was my wife's sister, Evelyn.

1:22:01.958 --> 1:22:04.375
Dear, kind woman.

1:22:04.375 --> 1:22:07.583
She died from, uh, complications in labor.

1:22:07.583 --> 1:22:08.500
He had a child?

1:22:09.625 --> 1:22:11.291
Daughter. June.

1:22:13.250 --> 1:22:14.083
Junebug.

1:22:16.208 --> 1:22:17.750
Randy, what happened to him?

1:22:17.750 --> 1:22:21.208
Ramona and I never really wanted kids.

1:22:21.208 --> 1:22:24.666
Just always thought we'd travel,
see the world.

1:22:26.500 --> 1:22:29.458
But life had other plans for us.

1:22:29.458 --> 1:22:32.958
After Evelyn died,
Randy sort of fell apart, I guess.

1:22:33.541 --> 1:22:34.750
Took to drinking.

1:22:36.291 --> 1:22:40.958
Then one day, he showed up
at our house with little June,

1:22:41.666 --> 1:22:44.583
said he had an appointment,
needed us to watch her,

1:22:45.250 --> 1:22:46.750
but he never came back.

1:22:47.333 --> 1:22:50.333
Just left that poor little girl with us.
She was four.

1:22:50.333 --> 1:22:53.583
Nobody ever heard from
or saw that man again.

1:22:53.583 --> 1:22:56.791
Maybe something happened,
like an accident or--

1:22:56.791 --> 1:23:00.833
Police found his car
for sale at a used lot,

1:23:00.833 --> 1:23:04.750
uh, his watch at a pawn shop.

1:23:05.333 --> 1:23:06.875
He took my shirt,

1:23:07.458 --> 1:23:09.375
my driver's license.

1:23:10.000 --> 1:23:12.541
Might have used that
to change his identity.

1:23:14.916 --> 1:23:16.291
What do you think happened?

1:23:16.291 --> 1:23:19.583
My guess, uh, drank himself to death.

1:23:20.166 --> 1:23:21.541
Suicide, maybe. Who knows?

1:23:21.541 --> 1:23:25.333
It's... it's hard to feel much sympathy
for somebody like that,

1:23:25.333 --> 1:23:28.375
abandoning their own motherless child.

1:23:28.375 --> 1:23:30.458
I can't think of a greater sin than that.

1:23:30.458 --> 1:23:31.458
No.

1:23:32.541 --> 1:23:34.833
No. No, no. No way.
He wouldn't do something like that.

1:23:34.833 --> 1:23:37.791
You said it yourself.
He can't remember, right?

1:23:39.291 --> 1:23:44.208
Maybe the reason he can't remember,
because the truth, what he did,

1:23:45.083 --> 1:23:46.416
is too unbearable.

1:23:56.083 --> 1:23:58.250
Randy? That's you, isn't it?

1:24:08.916 --> 1:24:10.083
Oh my God.

1:24:18.458 --> 1:24:20.583
Get away from me! Get away from me!

1:24:24.250 --> 1:24:25.875
Ernest! Get out of here!

1:24:30.166 --> 1:24:31.875
Get off me!

1:24:32.458 --> 1:24:34.000
- Get off me!

1:24:41.791 --> 1:24:42.708
Go to thermal!

1:24:45.625 --> 1:24:46.541
Light him up!

1:24:51.875 --> 1:24:53.958
Ernest! Stop!

1:24:55.333 --> 1:24:56.500
Stop!

1:24:57.083 --> 1:24:59.083
- Stop, you're hurting him!

1:25:00.541 --> 1:25:01.750
Ernest!

1:25:04.666 --> 1:25:07.125
Get your hands up! Hands up now!

1:25:07.125 --> 1:25:08.125
Get 'em up!

1:25:08.125 --> 1:25:09.125
Ernest, no!

1:25:11.708 --> 1:25:13.125
- On your feet, now!
- No.

1:25:24.333 --> 1:25:25.458
They have him.

1:25:26.333 --> 1:25:27.666
Where are you taking him?

1:25:29.291 --> 1:25:30.291
Ernest!

1:25:43.291 --> 1:25:44.291
Kevin.

1:25:47.958 --> 1:25:48.875
Are you okay?

1:25:48.875 --> 1:25:50.875
- Yeah. I'm fine.
<i>-</i> Did they hurt you?

1:25:50.875 --> 1:25:51.958
-  No.
- Are you sure?

1:25:52.583 --> 1:25:54.000
- Yeah.
- Let's get you home.

1:26:07.083 --> 1:26:09.041
I guess this worked out for you, huh?

1:26:09.041 --> 1:26:13.375
I think, considering the situation,
it's a pretty fair exchange, don't you?

1:26:14.916 --> 1:26:17.291
Now you and your family
can go live a normal life.

1:26:30.875 --> 1:26:32.333
- Hey.

1:26:36.625 --> 1:26:37.583
Sorry about your car.

1:26:38.625 --> 1:26:39.458
It's just a car.

1:26:40.958 --> 1:26:42.166
You good though?

1:26:45.625 --> 1:26:46.500
Yeah.

1:27:24.916 --> 1:27:28.625
I've been
waiting for this moment

1:27:30.083 --> 1:27:31.291
for so long.

1:27:58.500 --> 1:27:59.458
No, no, no.

1:28:00.625 --> 1:28:01.833
Stand down. I'm good.

1:28:07.916 --> 1:28:11.166
Come on, just right this way.
Ah, there she is.

1:28:11.958 --> 1:28:14.625
Ah, the woman of the hour.

1:28:15.291 --> 1:28:17.541
Gentlemen... Oh, and lady,

1:28:17.541 --> 1:28:20.666
please meet Dr. Leslie Monroe.

1:28:20.666 --> 1:28:23.583
Oh, actually, I correct myself.

1:28:23.583 --> 1:28:24.791
Agent Monroe.

1:28:24.791 --> 1:28:29.666
She assisted us in capturing
the asset you see before you.

1:28:29.666 --> 1:28:31.125
- Very good job, yes.

1:28:31.125 --> 1:28:32.083
Bravo.

1:28:32.083 --> 1:28:34.708
So, now--
No, please, please, just take a look.

1:28:41.708 --> 1:28:44.083
Of course you did more than just assist.
That was just--

1:28:44.083 --> 1:28:45.041
What's the endgame?

1:28:46.416 --> 1:28:48.583
-  I'm sorry, endgame?
-  Well...

1:28:51.208 --> 1:28:52.625
What are you gonna do with him?

1:28:52.625 --> 1:28:55.833
Well, he's dead, so, uh...

1:28:57.375 --> 1:28:58.708
whatever the hell we want.

1:29:27.833 --> 1:29:30.583
Hi, um, is Kevin around?

1:29:31.791 --> 1:29:33.125
I haven't seen him at school.

1:29:33.125 --> 1:29:36.250
Uh, yeah, he's just taking
a little break from stuff, honey.

1:29:36.750 --> 1:29:38.208
Maybe come back another time?

1:29:38.208 --> 1:29:39.666
Yeah, okay.

1:29:39.666 --> 1:29:40.916
It's okay, Mom.

1:29:44.083 --> 1:29:45.083
Hey.

1:29:45.750 --> 1:29:47.875
You haven't responded to any of my texts.

1:29:48.458 --> 1:29:49.541
Yeah, I...

1:29:50.541 --> 1:29:54.916
I haven't really felt like
talking to anyone, so...

1:29:54.916 --> 1:29:56.833
It's okay. I get it.

1:30:00.833 --> 1:30:01.666
How is everything?

1:30:02.291 --> 1:30:06.083
Well, I'm grounded until I'm 80,
but other than that, super peachy.

1:30:08.958 --> 1:30:12.083
Um, I just... I wanted to check up on you.

1:30:15.041 --> 1:30:15.958
Cool.

1:30:17.458 --> 1:30:18.625
Thanks.

1:30:18.625 --> 1:30:20.333
No, really though. Are you doing okay?

1:30:23.166 --> 1:30:24.000
Yeah.

1:30:25.916 --> 1:30:26.791
I'm fine.

1:30:29.416 --> 1:30:30.458
See you around.

1:30:53.166 --> 1:30:54.041
Hey.

